services.title: Barangay Clearance
services.description: Certificate issued by the barangay certifying that you are a resident in good standing with no pending cases. Required for employment, business permits, police clearance, and other transactions.

requirements.name: Valid Government-Issued ID
requirements.description: Any valid Philippine ID (Passport, Driver's License, PhilHealth, SSS, Voter's ID, etc.)

requirements.name: Proof of Residency
requirements.description: Utility bill, lease contract, or voter's certification

requirements.name: Community Tax Certificate (Cedula)
requirements.description: Current year CTC

requirements.name: 1x1 or 2x2 ID Photo
requirements.description: Recent photo, 1 copy

fees.name: Barangay Clearance Fee
fees.description: Standard fee (may vary slightly per barangay)

steps.title: Go to your barangay hall
steps.description: Visit during office hours (8 AM - 5 PM, Mon-Fri)

steps.title: Request application form
steps.description: Ask for barangay clearance application form at the counter

steps.title: Fill out form
steps.description: Complete the form with accurate information

steps.title: Submit requirements
steps.description: Present valid ID and proof of residency

steps.title: Pay fee
steps.description: Pay ₱50 barangay clearance fee at the treasurer

steps.title: Wait for processing
steps.description: Certificate will be prepared

steps.title: Claim clearance
steps.description: Receive your barangay clearance with official receipt

contact.phone: Contact your Barangay Captain or visit your barangay hall

services.title: Business Permit Application
services.description: Apply for new business permits or renew existing permits for your establishment in Kabankalan City. Mayor's Permit required to legally operate any business.

requirements.name: Barangay Business Clearance
requirements.description: Clearance from the barangay where business is located

requirements.name: DTI/SEC/CDA Registration
requirements.description: Business registration certificate from DTI (sole proprietor), SEC (corporation), or CDA (cooperative)

requirements.name: Community Tax Certificate (Cedula)
requirements.description: Current year cedula of business owner

requirements.name: Fire Safety Inspection Certificate
requirements.description: Certificate from Bureau of Fire Protection (BFP)

requirements.name: Contract of Lease or Land Title
requirements.description: Proof of ownership or lease of business location

requirements.name: Location Sketch/Map
requirements.description: Showing exact location of business

requirements.name: Valid ID of Owner
requirements.description: Government-issued ID, original and photocopy

requirements.name: Sanitary Permit
requirements.description: From City Health Office (for food and health-related businesses)

fees.name: Business Tax
fees.description: Varies based on gross sales/receipts and business type
fees.formula: Based on business category and gross sales

fees.name: Mayor's Permit Fee
fees.description: Minimum fee, varies by business category

steps.title: Secure Barangay Business Clearance
steps.description: Get clearance from barangay where business is located

steps.title: Register Business Name
steps.description: Register with DTI (sole proprietor), SEC (corporation), or CDA (cooperative)

steps.title: Get Cedula
steps.description: Secure Community Tax Certificate from City Treasurer

steps.title: Submit to BPLO
steps.description: Submit complete requirements to Business Permits and Licensing Office at City Hall

steps.title: Pay Assessed Fees
steps.description: Pay business tax and other fees at City Treasurer's Office

steps.title: Get Fire & Sanitary Permits
steps.description: Secure Fire Safety Certificate from BFP and Sanitary Permit from City Health (if applicable)

steps.title: Return to BPLO
steps.description: Submit fire and sanitary permits to BPLO

steps.title: Claim Business Permit
steps.description: Receive approved Business Permit and Plate Number

location.name: Kabankalan City Hall - Business Permits and Licensing Office (BPLO)

address.street: Justice Jesus Y. Perez Memorial Highway

services.title: Community Tax Certificate (Cedula)
services.description: Individual cedula/community tax certificate required for various transactions, employment, business permits, and legal documents.

requirements.name: Valid Government ID
requirements.description: Any government-issued identification, original and photocopy

requirements.name: Proof of Income
requirements.description: For employed: Salary slip, ITR, Certificate of Employment, or Affidavit of Income

requirements.name: Proof of Residency
requirements.description: Barangay certificate, utility bill, or lease contract

steps.title: Go to City Treasurer's Office
steps.description: Visit City Treasurer's Office at Kabankalan City Hall

steps.title: Fill out CTC Application
steps.description: Complete Community Tax Certificate application form

steps.title: Present Documents
steps.description: Submit valid ID and supporting documents (income proof, residency)

steps.title: Tax Computation
steps.description: Tax will be computed based on your declared income

steps.title: Pay at Cashier
steps.description: Pay computed tax (minimum ₱20 = ₱5 base + ₱15 stamp)

steps.title: Receive Cedula
steps.description: Get your Community Tax Certificate immediately

services.title: Birth Certificate (PSA Copy)
services.description: Request authenticated copy of birth certificate from the Philippine Statistics Authority (PSA). Required for employment, passport, marriage, and other legal purposes.

requirements.name: Valid Government ID
requirements.description: Original and photocopy (Passport, Driver's License, PhilHealth, SSS, Voter's ID, etc.)

requirements.name: Filled-out PSA Application Form
requirements.description: Available at the office or download from PSA website

requirements.name: Payment Fee
requirements.description: ₱155 for PSA authenticated copy

fees.name: PSA Authenticated Birth Certificate
fees.description: Official PSA copy with security paper

steps.title: Fill out PSA Application
steps.description: Complete PSA application form with accurate information

steps.title: Present Valid ID
steps.description: Submit valid government-issued ID

steps.title: Pay Fees
steps.description: Pay ₱155 at the Cashier's Office

steps.title: Receive Claim Stub
steps.description: Get official receipt and claim stub with tracking number

steps.title: Wait for PSA Processing
steps.description: PSA will process and deliver certificate

steps.title: Claim Certificate
steps.description: Return with claim stub and valid ID to claim certificate

requirements.name: Child's Birth Certificate
requirements.description: For infant and child vaccination programs

requirements.name: Immunization Record/Card

fees.name: Basic Health Consultation

fees.name: Vaccination Services
fees.description: Completely FREE under national immunization program (EPI)

fees.name: Medical Certificate
fees.description: For employment, school, or other requirements

steps.description: Go to Kabankalan City Health Office or nearest Rural Health Unit

steps.title: Register at Reception
steps.description: Fill out patient information form

steps.title: Wait for Assessment
steps.description: Wait for your turn to be called

steps.title: Consultation/Vaccination
steps.description: Receive medical consultation or vaccination service

steps.title: Get Records
steps.description: Receive updated health records or immunization card

services.title: Real Property Tax Payment
services.description: Pay your annual real property tax for land and building ownership in Kabankalan City. Payment deadline is typically by March 31 each year to avoid penalties.

requirements.name: Tax Declaration
requirements.description: Current tax declaration of property

requirements.name: Previous Official Receipt
requirements.description: Last year's tax payment receipt (if available)

requirements.name: Valid ID
requirements.description: Government-issued identification of property owner

fees.name: Property Tax
fees.description: Based on assessed property value (varies per property)
fees.formula: Computed based on property assessment and tax rate

fees.name: Penalty (if late)
fees.description: 2% penalty per month after March 31 deadline

steps.title: Prepare Documents
steps.description: Get tax declaration and previous year's receipt

steps.title: Go to City Treasurer
steps.description: Visit City Treasurer's Office at City Hall

steps.title: Present Documents
steps.description: Submit tax declaration and valid ID

steps.title: Tax Computation
steps.description: Staff will compute tax based on property assessment

steps.title: Pay at Cashier
steps.description: Pay computed real property tax

steps.title: Get Official Receipt
steps.description: Receive official receipt as proof of payment

address.street: Justice Jesus Y. Perez Memorial Highway, Kabankalan City Hall
